     "source": [
      "What is a Robot?\n",
      "- Actuators (motors) +\n",
      "- Sensors (position) +\n",
      "- Feedback (BRAINS)\n",
      "\n",
      "Chassis the \"Robot\" - mobile beer serving unit\n",
      "- No python\n",
      "- No feedback\n",
      "- Uses remote control\n",
      "- Not a good robot\n",
      "\n",
      "TCHO\n",
      "- Chocolate Factory in SF\n",
      "- Remote control of process equipment\n",
      "- People from WIRED\n",
      "\n",
      "Inside TCHO:\n",
      "- iPhone App (web server with nice formatting)\n",
      "- Apache + MySQL + Python (sockets, pyserial)\n",
      "- Comtrol Ethernet->Serial\n",
      "- Feedback control for heaters and actuators\n",
      "- With FXPAL: Bee Lieu, Maribeth Back\n",
      "\n",
      "Feedback:\n",
      "- Adjust drive with PID Controller\n",
      "- Not necessarily a job for python (do on bare metal)\n",
      "\n",
      "Python in robot stack:\n",
      "- High Level (Python) <-(command, query)-> Feedback PID Controller (bare metal) <-(control, sensor)-> Hardware\n",
      "- PID Controller + Hardware = Robot\n",
      "\n",
      "SWARM\n",
      "- Clever feedback controller off the shelf\n",
      "- Zigbee Wireless from python (wxPython)\n",
      "\n",
      "Robotic Desklams with wxPython\n",
      "- Joystick control desk lams\n",
      "- Hobby servos\n",
      "- Use pyserial\n",
      "- Feedback from hobby servo\n",
      "\n",
      "Actuators:\n",
      "- Motors (DC, brushless, steppers)\n",
      "- Motor Drivers (ESC, VFD, stepper drivers)\n",
      "- Servomotors (driver feedback included, hobby, fancy)\n",
      "\n",
      "Sensors:\n",
      "- Switches for touch and limit sensing\n",
      "- Position encoders (relative (optical), absolute (resistive, magnetic))\n",
      "- IR Sensors: reflectance\n",
      "- Ultrasonic distance and position\n",
      "- Cameras and structured light (Kinect)\n",
      "- LIDAR\n",
      "\n",
      "WAVE\n",
      "- Coachella 2012\n",
      "- Charlie Gadeken & WAVE crew\n",
      "- 12 hydrolic servo actuators\n",
      "- 35000 lbs\n",
      "- joint has angle sensor\n",
      "- Board has feedback\n",
      "\n",
      "Procept Biorobotics Inc.\n",
      "- \"Aquablation\" - position control via Python\n",
      "- Expensive swiss motor controllers\n",
      "\n",
      "How do we talk to all this gear?\n",
      "- pySerial to the rescue!\n",
      "- import serial (+ USB-serial HW)\n",
      "- maybe FTDIlib\n",
      "- Python <-> pySerial <-> hardware\n",
      "\n",
      "Serial Hardware Layer\n",
      "- Clocked: TWI, I2C (use pyBusPirate)\n",
      "- Unclocked (USB-serial + pySerial):\n",
      "-- TTL-serial (Arduino, microcontroller)\n",
      "-- RS-232 (3 wires, large voltage swings)\n",
      "-- RS-422 (differential)\n",
      "-- RS-485 (3-state, multidrop)\n",
      "\n",
      "Serial Protocols\n",
      "- Custom (arduino, most COTS controllers)\n",
      "- MODBUS (industrial) (pymodbus + twisted)\n",
      "- DMX (theater & architectural lighting)\n",
      "- MIDI (musical Instrument Digital Interface)\n",
      "- CAN-bus (automotive)\n",
      "\n",
      "Formatting Serial Data\n",
      "- ASCII is great\n",
      "- ser.write(cmd), resp = ser.read()\n",
      "- Be careful with `\\r`, `\\n`\n",
      "- For Binary: bytearray.fromhex(\"de ad be ef 00\"); struct.pack(), struct.unpack()\n",
      "\n",
      "Coping with Asynchronouse HW\n",
      "- Send a command, results not instantaneous!\n",
      "- Need to not block, might need to abort\n",
      "- select()\n",
      "- thread + Callback (GIL ok because I/O bound)\n",
      "- pyDispatcher\n",
      "- wsPython:wxEvt\n",
